      title: "The Now Trap",
      teaser:
        "Your present-moment orientation is your greatest gift and your most dangerous liability. When the current experience is rich enough — and for you, it almost always is — the future ceases to feel real. Not theoretically; viscerally. Planning feels like leaving the party early. Delayed gratification feels like a scam invented by people who don't know how to live. The cost accumulates invisibly until it's no longer invisible.",
